Тест Дики фуллера и автокореляция¶

In [51]:
from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf, plot_pacf
plt.rcParams.update({'figure.figsize':(15,11)})
def stc(df):
    alpha = 0.5
    print('    :')
    dftest = adfuller(df)
    dfoutput = pd.Series(dftest[0:4], index=['Test Statistic','p-value','#Lags Used','Number of Observations Used'])
    for key,value in dftest[4].items():
        dfoutput['Critical Value (%s)'%key] = value
    print(round(dfoutput,5))
    if dfoutput[1] < alpha :
        print(' , p-value  {:0.3f}'.format(alpha))
    elif dfoutput[1] > alpha:
        print('  , p-value    {:0.3f}'.format(alpha))
    print()
        
def dd(df):
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 2)
    axes[0, 0].plot(df); axes[0, 0].set_title('Original Series')
    plot_acf(df, ax=axes[0, 1])
    
    print('wihout')
    stc(df.dropna())
    
    # 1st Differencing
    axes[1, 0].plot(df.diff()); axes[1, 0].set_title('1st Order Differencing')
    plot_acf(df.diff().dropna(), ax=axes[1, 1])
    
    print('1st Differencing')
    stc(df.diff().diff().dropna())

    # 2nd Differencing
    axes[2, 0].plot(df.diff().diff()); axes[2, 0].set_title('2nd Order Differencing')
    plot_acf(df.diff().diff().dropna(), ax=axes[2, 1])
    
    print('1st Differencing')
    stc(df.diff().dropna())

    plt.show()

def co2(df):
    """
       
    """
    df = df[df['type'] == 'CO2'][['A.  Mineral industry',
       'B.  Chemical industry', 'C.  Metal industry',
       'D.  Non-energy products from fuels and solvent use']].copy()
    ###
    df = df['A.  Mineral industry']
    dd(df)
    return df
df = co2(df)

SARIMA¶

In [56]:
import pmdarima as pm

smodel = pm.auto_arima(df, start_p=1, start_q=1,
                         test='adf',
                         max_p=3, max_q=3, m=12,
                         start_P=0, seasonal=True,
                         d=None, D=1, trace=True,
                         error_action='ignore',  
                         suppress_warnings=True, 
                         stepwise=True)

smodel.summary()

# Forecast
n_periods = 16
fitted, confint = smodel.predict(n_periods=n_periods, return_conf_int=True)
index_of_fc = pd.date_range(df.index[-1], periods = n_periods, freq='YS')

# make series for plotting purpose
fitted_series = pd.Series(fitted, index=index_of_fc)
lower_series = pd.Series(confint[:, 0], index=index_of_fc)
upper_series = pd.Series(confint[:, 1], index=index_of_fc)

# Plot
plt.plot(df)
plt.plot(fitted_series, color='darkgreen')
plt.fill_between(lower_series.index, 
                 lower_series, 
                 upper_series, 
                 color='k', alpha=.15)

plt.title("SARIMA - Forecast of CO2 emissions")
plt.show()

Facebook prophet¶

In [59]:
#model prophet
def model_fb(df):
    df = df.copy()
    df = df.reset_index()
    df.columns = ['ds','y']
    m = Prophet()
    m.fit(df)
    future = m.make_future_dataframe(periods=15,freq='YS')
    forecast = m.predict(future)
    #fig1 = m.plot(forecast)
    return forecast
fb_data = model_fb(df)
